body:
What is the proper way to use SKTextBlobBuilder? 
I wrote this method and it throws `NullReferenceException`:
```
public static SKTextBlob GetTextBlob(string text)
{
	using SKTextBlobBuilder text_builder = new SKTextBlobBuilder();
	text_builder.AddRun(LabelTextFormat, 0, 0, text.Select(c => (ushort)c).ToArray());
	return text_builder.Build();
}
```
where `LabelTextFormat` is a SKPaint object; Note that I ensured neither the `text` nor the `LabelTextFormat` is null when the method is executed. 

I then discovered that if I set the `TextEncoding` property of the paint to `SKTextEncoding.GlyphId`, the method works fine, no exception.

Another problem is that, if I keep the encoding to `SKTextEncoding.GlyphId`, the text isn't rendered correctly. Strange characters appears instead of the text provided.
